### ============================================================
### Meta Chatbot Webhook PoC — HTTP test file
### Use with VS Code REST Client or JetBrains HTTP Client.
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### ── 1. Webhook Verification (GET /webhook) ──────────────────
### Simulates the handshake Meta performs when you save the
### webhook URL in the Meta App Dashboard.
### Replace VERIFY_TOKEN with the value in appsettings.json.

GET {{baseUrl}}/webhook?hub.mode=subscribe&hub.verify_token=YOUR_VERIFY_TOKEN&hub.challenge=CHALLENGE_STRING_123
Accept: text/plain

###

### ── 2. Send a Facebook Message (POST /api/send) ─────────────
### Sends a text reply to a Facebook user by their PSID.
### Replace USER_PSID with a real sender ID from a webhook log.

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "platform": "facebook",
  "recipientId": "USER_PSID",
  "message": "Hello from the PoC chatbot! (Facebook)"
}

###

### ── 3. Send an Instagram Message (POST /api/send) ──────────
### Sends a text reply to an Instagram user by their IGSID.

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "platform": "instagram",
  "recipientId": "USER_IGSID",
  "message": "Hello from the PoC chatbot! (Instagram)"
}

###

### ── 4. Webhook Event — Simulate a Facebook message ──────────
### NOTE: The X-Hub-Signature-256 header below is a PLACEHOLDER.
### You must compute the real HMAC-SHA256 signature of the body
### before this will be accepted by the server.
###
### PowerShell to compute the signature:
###   $secret = "YOUR_APP_SECRET"
###   $body   = '{"object":"page","entry":[{"id":"PAGE_ID","time":1234567890,"messaging":[{"sender":{"id":"USER_PSID"},"recipient":{"id":"PAGE_ID"},"timestamp":1234567890,"message":{"mid":"m.test","text":"Hello bot!"}}]}]}'
###   $hmac   = New-Object System.Security.Cryptography.HMACSHA256
###   $hmac.Key = [Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes($secret)
###   $hash   = $hmac.ComputeHash([Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes($body))
###   "sha256=" + [BitConverter]::ToString($hash).Replace("-","").ToLower()
###
### Bash (macOS/Linux):
###   echo -n '<body>' | openssl dgst -sha256 -hmac 'YOUR_APP_SECRET'
###   Prefix the output with "sha256="

POST {{baseUrl}}/webhook
Content-Type: application/json
X-Hub-Signature-256: sha256=REPLACE_WITH_COMPUTED_SIGNATURE

{
  "object": "page",
  "entry": [
    {
      "id": "PAGE_ID",
      "time": 1234567890,
      "messaging": [
        {
          "sender":    { "id": "USER_PSID" },
          "recipient": { "id": "PAGE_ID" },
          "timestamp": 1234567890,
          "message": {
            "mid":  "m.test001",
            "text": "Hello bot!"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

###

### ── 5. Webhook Event — Simulate an Instagram message ────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/webhook
Content-Type: application/json
X-Hub-Signature-256: sha256=REPLACE_WITH_COMPUTED_SIGNATURE

{
  "object": "instagram",
  "entry": [
    {
      "id": "IG_ID",
      "time": 1234567890,
      "messaging": [
        {
          "sender":    { "id": "USER_IGSID" },
          "recipient": { "id": "IG_ID" },
          "timestamp": 1234567890,
          "message": {
            "mid":  "m.ig001",
            "text": "Hi from Instagram!"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

###

### ── 6. Webhook Event — Simulate a Facebook postback ─────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/webhook
Content-Type: application/json
X-Hub-Signature-256: sha256=REPLACE_WITH_COMPUTED_SIGNATURE

{
  "object": "page",
  "entry": [
    {
      "id": "PAGE_ID",
      "time": 1234567890,
      "messaging": [
        {
          "sender":    { "id": "USER_PSID" },
          "recipient": { "id": "PAGE_ID" },
          "timestamp": 1234567890,
          "postback": {
            "title":   "Get Started",
            "payload": "GET_STARTED"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

###
